<html>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <title>Spanish by Hari</title>
  <div class = "chome">
    <h2> Spanish by Hari</h2>
  </div>
    <div class = "column third">
    <h4>
    Paste in the text in Spanish in the box to the right and click go. <br><hr>
    Hover over a word to get a live translation from SpanishDict. This could be a homonym, so watch out! <br><hr>
    Click on the word to see its definition on SpanishDict. <br><hr>
    To get a phrase, highlight a series of words and check the live translator. If no result pops, click the live translator to get redirected to SpanishDict. <br><hr>
    Hit the 's' key to add the text of the live translator to your saved list. Hit 'e' to download your saved list.<br><hr>
    </h4>
    </div>
    <div class = "column chome">
    <form method="POST" action="/create">
      <textarea id = "texter" name = "texter"></textarea><br>
      <input class = "button" type="submit" value="Go">
    </form>
    <br>
    </div>
